body_html:
Later commits 8fdb974 and its successor 5563229 do build properly (caveat: the giflib link seems broken). The master I have used on this "dichotomy" breaks (f6e0f64).

I picked 8fdb974 for testing due to modification related to the duplicate symbols in the next commit (5563229). Unfortunately this did not pin-point the issue.

It seems the problem is "indirect". Perhaps some wildcard somewhere includes twice the same file (there was a similar issue in the Makefile in tensorflow/contrib/makefile), or an issue with how the extern declaration is used by the build system (e.g. in tensorflow/core/public/version.h). Just a guess. Hope this serves.

body:
Later commits 8fdb974 and its successor 5563229 do build properly (caveat: the `giflib` link seems broken). The master I have used on this "dichotomy" breaks (f6e0f64f).

I picked 8fdb974 for testing due to modification related to the duplicate symbols in the next commit (5563229). Unfortunately this did not pin-point the issue.

It seems the problem is "indirect". Perhaps some wildcard somewhere includes twice the same file (there was a similar issue in the `Makefile` in `tensorflow/contrib/makefile`), or an issue with how the `extern` declaration is used by the build system (e.g. in `tensorflow/core/public/version.h`). Just a guess. Hope this serves.
